BEIJING , September 5 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- President Jiang Zemin , meeting today with Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto , urged Japan to respect China 's stance on the Taiwan issue .
Jiang reiterated the Chinese government stand that Taiwan is an inalienable part of Chinese territory and that the Taiwan issue is China 's internal affair that no other country has the right to interfere in .
He said the Japanese government has political obligations and made a solemn promise on the issue of Taiwan in the China - Japan Joint Statement and the China - Japan Treaty of Peace and Friendship .
For historical reasons , any Japanese action related to Taiwan would affect the feelings of the Chinese people , Jiang said , and China hopes that Japan will respect the Chinese position on this and act cautiously .
Hashimoto said Japan does not support `` two Chinas '' , nor does it support Taiwan independence .
Japan holds that Taiwan , as part of China , is not qualified at all to enter the United Nations , and his government 's stand on this is clear-cut .
On behalf of the Japanese government , Hashimoto invited Jiang for a state visit to Japan next year , which will be the 20th anniversary of the China - Japan Treaty of Peace and Friendship .
Jiang thanked him for the invitation .
